title: Oyster Beignets With A Sorrel Velouté
summary: Need a pescatarian main course? Oyster Beignets With A Sorrel Velouté could be an outstanding recipe to try. One serving contains 716 calories, 18g of protein, and 46g of fat. For $4.22 per serving, this recipe covers 23% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. This recipe serves 2. Only a few people made this recipe, and 1 would say it hit the spot. A mixture of banana shallots, juice of lemon, olive oil, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so flavorful. To use up the cornflour you could follow this main course with the Cherry and Apricot Cobbler as a dessert. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 48%. This score is good. Try John Dory Oyster Bar Oyster Pan Roast with Uni Butter Crostini, Asparagus Velouté, and Cauliflower Velouté for similar recipes.
